	<element name="Cunning Tracker" type="Class Feature" source="Purple Aether Games" id="ID_JACOBSKELLOGG_DMSG_CLASS_FEATURE_CUNNINGTRACKER">
		<description>
			<p>Your sharpness of mind makes you a formidable hunter of any prey. Starting at 1st level, whenever you make a Wisdom (Survival) check to track one or more creatures, you can add your Intelligence modifier to the check.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
			<description>Whenever you make a Wisdom (Survival) check to track one or more creatures, you can add your Intelligence modifier to the check.</description>
        </sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Poisoner" type="Class Feature" source="Purple Aether Games" id="ID_JACOBSKELLOGG_DMSG_CLASS_FEATURE_POISONER">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at 2nd level, you are well-versed in the use of poison, granting you several benefits:</p>
			<p>First, you have advantage on any ability checks you make to harvest or create poisons. Second, the gold and time you must spend to create a dose of poison is halved. Finally, you can apply a dose of poison to a weapon or ammunition as a bonus action instead of an action.</p>
        </description>
		<sheet>
			<description>You have advantage on any ability checks you make to harvest or create poisons. Also, the gold and time you must spend to create a dose of poison is halved. Finally, you can apply a dose of poison to a weapon or ammunition as a bonus action instead of an action.</description>
        </sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Slayer's Focus" type="Class Feature" source="Purple Aether Games" id="ID_JACOBSKELLOGG_DMSG_CLASS_FEATURE_SLAYERS_FOCUS">
		<description>
			<p>Also at 2nd level, you learn how to use your wits when engaging your target. You can use a bonus action to designate one creature you can see as your quarry. This effect remains in place until you finish a long rest, but ends early if you are incapacitated or if you use this ability again.</p>
            <p class="indent">Additionally, You can add your Intelligence modifier to any Wisdom (Perception) checks you make to find your quarry, as well as to the damage dealt by your weapon attacks against it.</p>
			<p>This bonus damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 11th level in this class, and by another 1d6 (2d6) when you reach 17th level.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet usage="Bonus Action">
			<description> You can use a bonus action to designate one creature you can see as your quarry. This effect remains in place until you finish a long rest, but ends early if you are incapacitated or if you use this ability again. Also, add your Intelligence modifier to any Wisdom (Perception) checks you make to find your quarry, as well as to the damage dealt by your weapon attacks against it. The bonus damage to your quarry increases by 1d6 at 11th level in this class, and by 2d6 at 17th level.</description>
		</sheet>
    </element>
	<element name="Ambusher" type="Class Feature" source="Purple Aether Games" id="ID_JACOBSKELLOGG_DMSG_CLASS_FEATURE_AMBUSHER">
		<description>
		    <p>Beginning at 3rd level, you are adept at getting the jump on your foes. You can add your Intelligence modifier to your initiative rolls.</p>
		        <p class="indent">Additionally, once per turn when you use the Attack action to attack the target of your slayer's focus feature, if that creature hasn't taken a turn in the combat yet or is unaware of your attack, you can make one additional weapon attack against the same creature as part of the same action.</p>
        </description>
		<sheet>
			<description>Add your Intelligence modifier to your initiative rolls. In addition, once per turn when you use the Attack action to attack the target of your slayer's focus feature, if that creature hasn't taken a turn in the combat yet or is unaware of your attack, you can make one additional weapon attack against the same creature as part of the same action. </description>
        </sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Slayer's Specialty" type="Class Feature" source="Purple Aether Games" id="ID_JACOBSKELLOGG_DMSG_CLASS_FEATURE_SLAYERS_SPECIALITY">
		<description>
			<p>Your career as a slayer can take many forms, represented by a specialty you choose at 3rd level: the Bounty Hunter, the Ghostkiller, the Monster Hunter, the Ninja or the Fiend Hunter.</p>
            <p class="indent">Your specialty grants you features when you choose it at 3rd level, and again at 7th, 13th, and 18th level.</p>
		</description>
